	```python

	print( round(8/3,2)) 
```
- instead of round , use format fxn
	```python
	#round
	bill=round(bill,2)
	#format
	bill= {.2f}.format(bill)
```

	```python
	print(21.6666//2)                #rounds to 10.0
```

# Type casting
- from one data type to another
```python
str(), int() , float() , bool()

#ex
name= "Kavya"
age =25
gpa =3.2
is_student= True
  
gpa= int(gpa)
print(type(gpa))
print(gpa)
  
age=str(age)
print(type(age))
  
is_student=str(is_student)
print(is_student)
print(type(is_student))

name=bool(name)
print(name)          # True

```
